uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.parquetstore.operation.handler.spark.utilities

Class WriteData

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.parquetstore.operation.handler.spark.utilities.WriteData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.spark.api.java.function.VoidFunction<Iterator<Element>>

    public class WriteData
extends Object
implements org.apache.spark.api.java.function.VoidFunction<Iterator<Element>>
    A VoidFunction that writes an Iterator of Elements to multiple Parquet files, with one file per group. Each file is initially named using both the partition id and the task attempt id. This name is unique across multiple simultaneous calls of this function for the same partition. This ensures that tasks that are processing the same partition do not attempt to write to the same file. Once all the data from the Iterator has been written, the files are closed. Each file is then renamed to input-partitionId.parquet. If a FileAlreadyExistsException is thrown, this is ignored as it means that another task has already completed writing this file and so the results of this task are not needed.
